trend_summary: Across the series the built footprint spreads outward and packs inward. Industrial parks grow along the western highway, new housing fills eastern gaps, and a large interchange appears south-centre. Farmland and forest in the north and west recede, while small internal green spaces are retained or landscaped.
notable_changes: Industrial/commercial estates enlarge west of the main highway corridor.
Residential infill replaces vacant plots in the eastern neighbourhoods.
New cloverleaf-style interchange and connecting roads built in the south-central area.
Progressive loss of farmland along the northern and western fringes.
Forest blocks become fragmented, offset by minor park landscaping within the urban core.
